    <p>Be­tween 5 Cows And The Deep Blue Sea</p>
    <p>In this drama­tised read­ing by</p>
    <p>Brown Voices, Girl walks a tightrope be­tween tra­di­tional ar­ranged mar­riages and to­day’s mod­ern dat­ing cul­ture as she strug­gles to es­tab­lish her iden­tity and in­de­pen­dence.</p>
    <p>Brown Voices is Sin­ga­pore’s first col­lec­tive of In­dian theatre prac­ti­tion­ers and play­wrights that sup­ports, en­cour­ages and trains the writ­ing of qual­ity scripts for the stage. As there is some ma­ture con­tent and coarse lan­guage, this read­ing is rec­om­mended for those aged 16 years and older.</p>
    <p>es­planade.com</p>
    <p>Till Sept 11, 4pm</p>
    <p>Free</p>
    <p>baca skrip: #Cause­way</p>
    <p>This is an on­line Malay read­ing of Al­fian Sa’at’s ear­lier work that ex­plores the re­la­tion­ship be­tween Sin­ga­pore and its clos­est neigh­bour, Malaysia. Writ­ten at age 21, it won him a Com­men­da­tion Award by the Malay Lan­guage Coun­cil in 1998. Con­sist­ing of eight chap­ters per­formed by a cast of seven, the read­ing will take the au­di­ence on a tour of com­mon his­to­ries and shared pop cul­ture. In Malay with ac­com­pa­ny­ing Malay text and English sub­ti­tles.</p>
    <p>Aug 28, 8pm</p>
    <p>$10 ba­caskrip­cause­way.peatix.com</p>


